title: Population of Spain in 2019 by gender and autonomous community
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 19 different Communitys on X-axis for 2 groups Male, and Female. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Population.
Out of all 2 groups, Female had the highest Population in Community Andalusia and Female had the lowest Population in Community Ceuta.
In Community Andalusia, Male had the highest Population among all 19 Communitys and it has the lowest Population in Community Melilla.
There is a gap of 4126403.0 between the highest and lowest Population found for Male in Community Andalusia and Melilla.

Community Andalusia had the maximum Population among all 2 groups, and it was for Female. The minimum Population was observed in Community Ceuta for Female.
